Shopify has dominated ecommerce infrastructure for over a decade. But dominance breeds complacency, and competitors like BigCommerce, WooCommerce, and the new wave of headless solutions have been gunning for market share. After running 47 storefronts on Shopify across our team's portfolio—spanning apparel, specialty food, fitness equipment, and salon retail—we can report on what actually holds up under pressure and what breaks when you scale beyond a single location.

